## Laravel Architecture
```
app/
├── Http/
│   ├── Controllers/     # Thin — delegate to services only
│   ├── Requests/        # Form request validation classes
│   ├── Resources/       # API resource transformers
│   └── Middleware/
├── Services/            # Business logic (one service per domain)
├── Repositories/        # Data access layer (interfaces + implementations)
├── Models/              # Eloquent models (relationships, scopes, casts)
├── Jobs/                # Queued background jobs
├── Events/ + Listeners/ # Event-driven architecture
├── Exceptions/          # Custom exception classes
└── Observers/           # Model observers for audit logging
```

## Code Standards
```php
// ✅ Correct — thin controller
class UserController extends Controller
{
    public function __construct(private UserService $userService) {}

    public function store(CreateUserRequest $request): JsonResponse
    {
        $result = $this->userService->createUser($request->validated());
        return response()->json(['success' => true, 'data' => new UserResource($result)], 201);
    }
}

// ✅ Correct — service with transaction + state machine
class UserService
{
    public function createUser(array $data): User
    {
        return DB::transaction(function () use ($data) {
            $user = User::updateOrCreate(
                ['email' => $data['email']],
                ['status' => UserStatus::PENDING, ...$data]
            );
            // Idempotent — same email returns existing record, not duplicate
            if ($user->status === UserStatus::ACTIVE) {
                throw new UserAlreadyExistsException('User already registered.');
            }
            event(new UserCreated($user)); // Event-driven — listener sends email
            return $user;
        });
    }
}
```

## Eloquent Performance Rules
- Eager loading mandatory: always use `with()` to prevent N+1
- Select only needed columns: `->select(['id', 'name', 'email'])`
- Chunk for large datasets: `->chunk(200, fn($users) => ...)`
- Cursor for streaming: `->cursor()` on memory-sensitive operations
- Indexes: define in migrations, match query patterns
- Never use `all()` on large tables — always paginate

## Queue Rules
- All operations > 800ms → dispatch to queue (never block HTTP response)
- Failed jobs → retry 3 times with exponential backoff
- Failed after retries → log to `failed_jobs` table + notify admin
- Job classes: one responsibility, max 50 lines
- Horizon for queue monitoring in production

## Validation Rules
- Dedicated Form Request class for every endpoint
- Custom validation messages in plain English (user-facing)
- Validate at entry point (controller) — never in service/model
- Custom validation rules for complex business logic

## Security Mandatory Checklist
- [ ] Mass assignment: `$fillable` defined on every model
- [ ] SQL: Eloquent only or parameterized queries (no raw string concat)
- [ ] Auth: Sanctum (SPA/mobile) or Passport (OAuth)
- [ ] Rate limiting: throttle middleware on auth and sensitive endpoints
- [ ] Sensitive data: encrypted in DB (Laravel's encrypted cast)
- [ ] Logs: never log passwords, tokens, or PII

## API Resource Transformation
```php
// Always transform — never return raw Eloquent model
class UserResource extends JsonResource
{
    public function toArray(Request $request): array
    {
        return [
            'id' => $this->id,
            'name' => $this->name,
            'email' => $this->email,
            'status' => $this->status,
            'createdAt' => $this->created_at->toISOString(),
            // Never expose: password, remember_token, internal IDs
        ];
    }
}
```
